   102	
   103	---
   104	
   105	## Staged Gate Scaffolding (Current Non-Blocking Contract)
   106	
   107	While the Rust testing cutover is in progress, staged gate scaffolds are
   108	available in `justfile` and exercised by CI:
   109	
   110	```bash
   111	just check-phase0-scenario-stage
   112	just check-phase0-bdd-smoke
   113	just check-phase0-bdd-wave-a
   114	just check-phase0-mutation-stage
   115	just check-phase0-coverage-stage
   116	just check-phase0-stage-gates
   117	```
   118	
   119	Current behavior:
   120	
   121	- commands are non-blocking scaffolds that emit readiness/status signals,
   122	- `check-phase0-bdd-smoke` executes a cucumber-rs smoke scenario and emits the
   123	  feature tag line as traceability evidence,
   124	- `check-phase0-bdd-wave-a` executes Wave A feature files (`1.1` through `3.2`)
   125	  and emits BEH-tag evidence for each file,
   126	- `check-phase0-mutation-stage` executes a sampled `cargo-mutants` run (when
   127	  installed) and writes machine-readable survivor triage to
   128	  `artifacts/phase0-mutation/staged/latest/triage.json`,
   129	- `check-phase0-coverage-stage` executes staged `cargo llvm-cov` behavior runs
   130	  (when installed) and writes machine-readable behavior-gap classification to
   131	  `artifacts/phase0-coverage/staged/latest/classification.json`,
   132	- they are intended for per-task demonstrability while implementation lands,
   133	- strict blocking enforcement remains a later cutover task.
   134	
   135	---
